# .aidocs/memory-update.aidocs - /memory-update Contract

Purpose
- Read project documentation and ingest structured knowledge into `/.MEMORY/` canonical categories.
- Separated from `/project-init` to keep each command focused (KISS).

When to use
- After `/project-init` has initialized the project (git + system files + empty memory structure).
- When project docs have changed and memory needs refreshing.
- When a new agent needs to understand the project quickly.

Contract
- Validate project is already initialized (`/.MEMORY/` exists).
- Discover project docs/router + relevant README/spec docs.
- Read source docs in order: root shared docs -> project entry files -> project docs/router -> relevant README/spec docs.
- Build topic map → create/update `/.MEMORY/domains/<topic>.md`.
- Ingest/restructure docs into canonical memory categories (merge/edit; no duplicates).
- Output ingestion coverage: read files, skipped files, reasons, mapping.

Safety
- Merge/edit only — never duplicate content.
- Do not overwrite user-authored memory content without explicit instruction.
- Re-read `/.MEMORY/NOW.md` before planning and after compaction/session resume.
- Log update outcome to today's daily file.
